ExpressionTree

Class Operator

  • java.lang.Object
    • ExpressionTree.Node
      • ExpressionTree.Operator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Addition, Assignment, Multiplication, Ternary, Unary

    public abstract class Operator
extends Node
    Node class which is a wrapper for any operation. It has methods for priority determination based on operation character. These are used mainly when parsing expression strings.

      • createOperator

        public static Operator createOperator(char operation,
                                      int columnNumber)
        Wrapper for constructors; they should not be called directly. This check the given symbol and creates the according operation instance.
        Parameters:
        operation - operation symbol
        columnNumber - column number
        Returns:
        node instance with the correct operation

      • evaluate

        public abstract Node evaluate()
        Evaluates a node in tree by performing the according operation.
        Returns:
        new constant node if operation is not assignment, or the same node with variable value changed if called for tree root

      • evaluateLeaves

        protected void evaluateLeaves()
        Calls evaluate method for both leaves (if they are not null). This way it leaves them evaluated as constants or variables which can be used to perform the node operation.

      • setPriority

        private int setPriority()
        Method called by the constructor. Sets the priority for current instance, and modifies sign for printing if needed.
        Returns:
        priority value or dummy value if symbol is not an operation (eg: "(")
